                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.51/670: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Representative on Special Mission in Cuba</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crowder</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-12-25T14:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 25, 1921—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:33 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>156. Reference to your December 24, 1 p.m. I concur in Department’s suggestion
                    and have notified President Zayas that my departure will be delayed until
                    decree, now in preparation, carrying further budget economies, is signed and
                    promulgated which he again said would be about January 1st.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Crowder</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
